==English==
===Interjection===
(Something) '''my arse'''!
# {{slang}}, {{UK}} Indicates [[disapproval]], [[disregard]], [[disdain]], [[disgust]] or [[disbelief]]. 
#:''Denise Royle: Dad! Your fly hole's all undone.''
#:''Jim Royle: Ah, the cage might be open, but the beast is asleep.''
#:''Barbara Royle: Beast '''my arse'''.'' - [[q:The Royle Family|The Royal Famly]]

